# Tower FDE Workflow Agent — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
LangGraph-based workflow agent for a Forward Deployed Engineer at Tower (Python-native serverless data stack on Apache Iceberg). Automates admin work across customer engagements: discovery, PoC prep, proposals, follow-up.

## Shared Source of Truth
- `MEMORY_BANK.md` — Architecture decisions, progress, patterns
- `.cursorrules` — This file
- `.agents/skills` — Antigravity agent skills

Read MEMORY_BANK.md before making architectural decisions.

## Code Standards

### Python
- Python 3.12+, use modern typing (PEP 695 style where possible)
- Use `uv` for package management (not pip/venv)
- Async-first: all graph nodes are `async def`
- Type hints on all function signatures
- No docstrings unless logic is non-obvious
- Pydantic for config (`pydantic-settings`), TypedDict for graph state

### Project Structure
- One file per graph node, each exports a single async function
- Subgraph wiring in `__init__.py` via factory functions (`build_X_subgraph()`)
- Prompts in `src/llm/prompts/` (Python) and `prompts/` (Markdown templates)
- Tests mirror `src/` structure

### LangGraph Patterns
- Use `interrupt()` inside nodes (LangGraph 0.4+), not `interrupt_before`
- State schema in `src/graph/state.py` — `CustomerState` is the single state type
- Model routing: `get_llm("fast")` for Haiku, `get_llm("strong")` for Sonnet
- OpenRouter via `langchain-openai` with `base_url="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"`
- SqliteSaver checkpointer, one thread per customer

### Knowledge Base
- ChromaDB embedded mode, 5 collections
- Local embeddings (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`), never API embeddings
- `retrieve_similar()` in `src/kb/store.py` — always use metadata filtering

### UI
- FastAPI + Jinja2 + HTMX, no SPA
- SSE for real-time graph execution status
- PicoCSS or Tailwind, no build step

### Testing
- Dummy email fixtures in `tests/fixtures/emails/` (JSON)
- No live Gmail in v1
- Mock LLM calls in tests via `conftest.py` fixtures

## Do NOT
- Use Anthropic API directly (use OpenRouter)
- Create SPA or React frontend
- Add PostgreSQL, Redis, or task queues
- Add live Gmail integration in v1
- Over-abstract — one-time operations don't need helpers
- Add comments/docstrings to unchanged code
